{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Place chickpea flour, water, oil and salt in mixing bowl then whisk <b>30 sec\/speed 4<b>. Transfer to a bowl and set aside to rest for 30 minutes. Meanwhile, rinse mixing bowl and continue with recipe.","Place onion, garlic and oil in mixing bowl and chop <b>3 sec\/speed 5<b>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula then sauté <b>5 min\/100°C\/speed <b>.","Add tomato, tuna, olives, capers, oregano and black pepper then chop <b>2 sec\/speed 5<b>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula and set aside while cooking pancake.","Preheat grill to 220°C. Pour enough olive oil into a large oven-proof non-stick frying pan to cover the base. Heat over a medium-high heat then pour in rested batter. Cook for 8-10 minutes until pancake starts to brown at the edges.","Place frying pan under grill for 8-10 minutes until brown on top.","Transfer pancake to a plate then arrange topping from mixing bowl over the top. Scatter with basil leaves then sprinkle with chilli flakes (if using). Slice into quarters and serve, with a salad if desired."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["120 g chickpea flour","250 g water","50 g olive oil, plus extra for frying","½ tsp fine sea salt","1 red onion, quartered","1 garlic clove","1 tomato, sliced","100 g tinned tuna in oil, drained and flaked","1 Tbsp pitted black olives","1 Tbsp pickled capers, drained and rinsed","1 pinch dried oregano","1 pinch ground black pepper","2 fresh basil leaves, shredded, for garnish","1 pinch chilli flakes              (optional)"]}],"id":"r235759","imageLink":"https:\/\/3.bp.blogspot.com\/-Ehss98xSKvE\/XZQvcZxdF8I\/AAAAAAAAccU\/8msPMqGfuT0uKhff6oGEENRjNklQGh8KwCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_FJyPks-u-dkLL3wy.png","title":"Socca with Tuna, Olives and Capers","publishedAt":"2017-10-02T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"55 g","fat":"66 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"73 g","calories":"4753 kJ \/ 1140 kcal"},"usefulItems":"large non-stick frying pan, grill, hob","hintsAndTricks":["Add half a red pepper (cut in quarters) in step 3.","Socca are crepes made from chickpea flour, a Provençal street food, cooked quickly on a sizzling griddle and eaten on the go. This version, which browns under the grill, is something between a sturdy crepe and a soft flatbread. The chickpea flour gives it a tender, almost custard-like texture. Serve warm as a light lunch or evening meal with accompaniments.","Makes one large pancake."],"basicInfo":["easy","25m","1h 5m","1 portion"]}